Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Speedy Indonesian Style King Prawn Noodles in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Noodles ==

Boil a full #kettle{}. Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a #large saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g} and broccoli to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

== Prawns ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Drain the @King Prawns{225%g}.

Once hot, add the prawns to the pan.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry for ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're opaque in the middle.

== Sauce ==

While the prawns cook, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}(trimmed and peeled). Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the prawns have cooked, add the garlic, @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and carrot ribbons. Stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Next, stir in the @Bulgogi Sauce{75%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} and @Water{2%tbsp}.

> See pantry for both amounts.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and cook until the sauce is slightly thickened, ~{1%minute}.

== Assembly ==

Stir the cooked noodles and broccoli into the frying pan until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash more @Water{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the noodles out between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} to finish. Enjoy!